review_blob: Bronze/Honey in color with a deep cherry aroma. Very sweet almost like a Reisling wine and scarily smooth going down. If you want your lady to try beer, this is it.
Found on tap at Firkin. Light golden color with a very citrusy aroma, slight hint of grapefruit. Heavy on hops, light on citrus flavor with a bit of bitter.
Tasted this at Taste of Cincinnati and it was pretty awful. Mainly tasted like raw green peanuts. Definately not what was expected.
One of the best Pumpkin Ales  Ive had. Nice crisp fall taste and pumpkin aroma. Dont put an orange in this one.
beer_name: Blue Moon Harvest Moon Pumpkin Ale
